WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.560 --> 00:00:09.993
Dear young people, we heard in the Gospel
how Jesus calls us to remain in His love.

00:00:09.993 --> 00:00:15.543
Last Sunday, Jesus similarly
spoke about love, but He set

00:00:15.543 --> 00:00:18.872
criteria for how we should love.

00:00:18.872 --> 00:00:24.422
We listened to that passage
of the Gospel on Sunday.

00:00:24.422 --> 00:00:32.191
Today, the word love is used so
frequently, but above all, it is used

00:00:32.191 --> 00:00:38.295
so incomprehensibly that everything and
anything is associated with love, even

00:00:38.295 --> 00:00:42.735
things that are not true love at all.

00:00:43.235 --> 00:00:49.451
And then Jesus not only gives this
commandment in the Gospel to remain

00:00:49.451 --> 00:00:56.145
in His love, but today He also
warns us about how we should love.

00:00:56.145 --> 00:01:03.318
Because often, we have our own criteria
for what love is and how to love.

00:01:03.318 --> 00:01:07.621
Love is portrayed in movies,
songs, poetry, literature, and

00:01:07.621 --> 00:01:13.360
relationships, but, as I said,
not all of it is true love.

00:01:13.360 --> 00:01:15.678
What is Jesus teaching us?

00:01:15.678 --> 00:01:22.172
So, we know that in the Old Testament
we have this commandment of love.

00:01:22.172 --> 00:01:26.810
And in two places it says,
"Love your God," how?

00:01:26.810 --> 00:01:32.839
"With all your heart." And then it
says, "Love yourself... Love your neighbor

00:01:32.839 --> 00:01:38.868
as you love yourself." And what is
the criterion for proper love here?

00:01:38.868 --> 00:01:40.260
It's not good.

00:01:40.260 --> 00:01:41.651
Jesus refines it.

00:01:41.651 --> 00:01:48.144
It's not good because what if someone
has a small heart, little love for

00:01:48.144 --> 00:01:55.101
God, it says, "Love God with all your
heart." What if someone has a closed

00:01:55.101 --> 00:02:01.595
heart, a stone heart, and the commandment
says, "Love God with all your heart?"

00:02:03.905 --> 00:02:10.792
What if the measure of love for
others is how much I love myself?

00:02:10.792 --> 00:02:14.727
Today, you young people,
50% don't love themselves.

00:02:14.727 --> 00:02:16.203
50% or more.

00:02:16.203 --> 00:02:24.567
So, how can it be a measure to love
my neighbor as I love myself when many

00:02:24.567 --> 00:02:31.454
despise their own lives, when they don't
love their own lives, and God commands

00:02:31.454 --> 00:02:35.390
us to love others as we love ourselves?

00:02:36.370 --> 00:02:39.506
However, these are commandments
from the Old Testament.

00:02:39.506 --> 00:02:43.036
That's why Jesus sets a
different criterion and says.

00:02:43.036 --> 00:02:49.310
And he said this at the Last Supper when
he was saying goodbye to his disciples.

00:02:52.150 --> 00:02:54.632
Love as I love you.

00:02:54.632 --> 00:03:00.092
So, what I explained earlier,
that's the criterion of human love.

00:03:00.092 --> 00:03:06.050
But Jesus doesn't want human
love to be our standard for love.

00:03:06.550 --> 00:03:09.542
And we can hear this a lot today.

00:03:09.542 --> 00:03:14.030
We talk about some kind of emotional
love that falls apart quickly.

00:03:14.030 --> 00:03:17.022
We talk about relationships
that break up frequently.

00:03:17.022 --> 00:03:21.137
And we see that we are not
talking about true love.

00:03:21.137 --> 00:03:27.121
Because we love on a human level,
as much as we can, and how we can,

00:03:27.121 --> 00:03:29.740
and we declare how long love lasts.

00:03:29.740 --> 00:03:32.228
Can love have an expiration date?

00:03:32.228 --> 00:03:33.058
It cannot.

00:03:33.058 --> 00:03:36.377
So why does it end for some people?

00:03:36.377 --> 00:03:39.281
Obviously, that wasn't
love; it was emotions.

00:03:39.281 --> 00:03:44.673
Many young people today follow their
emotions and declare them as some kind

00:03:44.673 --> 00:03:47.162
of love that breaks down frequently.

00:03:47.162 --> 00:03:50.066
But that's a human criterion for love.

00:03:50.066 --> 00:03:54.215
And Jesus says a new
commandment, he adds to this.

00:03:54.495 --> 00:03:56.917
Love as I have loved you.

00:03:56.917 --> 00:03:59.742
When did Jesus say this to them?

00:03:59.742 --> 00:04:05.394
He said it at the moment when everyone
had betrayed him, left him, when

00:04:05.394 --> 00:04:11.449
suffering lay ahead of him, when the
path of the cross lay ahead of him.

00:04:11.449 --> 00:04:16.697
When the agony in the Garden of
Gethsemane lay ahead of him, nothing

00:04:16.697 --> 00:04:19.120
shook Jesus to stop loving us.

00:04:19.700 --> 00:04:24.602
Neither crisis, nor persecution, nor
scourging—Jesus knows what is coming.

00:04:24.602 --> 00:04:30.975
He wants to say, remain steadfast
in your love for God because I

00:04:30.975 --> 00:04:38.328
love you so much that I will not
give up on you for any sacrifice.

00:04:38.328 --> 00:04:39.799
That is love.

00:04:39.799 --> 00:04:46.662
When we love at the cost of everything
that happens in our lives, at

00:04:46.662 --> 00:04:51.565
the cost of suffering, you cannot
separate love from suffering.

00:04:52.045 --> 00:04:55.308
Love cannot melt away in
suffering or misunderstanding.

00:04:55.308 --> 00:05:01.835
And that's why it's important to say at
the start of this sermon that many people

00:05:01.835 --> 00:05:04.691
still don't understand what true love is.

00:05:04.691 --> 00:05:09.994
Many still live in the Old Testament
and cling to this human dimension—how

00:05:09.994 --> 00:05:14.889
they love themselves, how they
love others, how they have a heart,

00:05:14.889 --> 00:05:17.337
that's how much they love God.

00:05:17.337 --> 00:05:19.785
However, Jesus teaches
us something different.

00:05:20.855 --> 00:05:27.744
A distorted image of love, my dear
ones, is often present in our lives.

00:05:27.744 --> 00:05:31.681
A distorted image of
love is often imposed.

00:05:31.681 --> 00:05:37.095
When some feeling melts away,
dissolves, and disappears, so does love.

00:05:37.095 --> 00:05:39.063
That is not love.

00:05:39.063 --> 00:05:42.016
Love is where the cross is.

00:05:42.016 --> 00:05:47.430
The first thing that Jesus
encourages us to do in today's

00:05:47.430 --> 00:05:50.875
gospel is to remain in his love.

00:05:50.875 --> 00:05:54.320
And he says, remain in my love.

00:05:54.940 --> 00:05:58.532
And how will you, he says, remain?

00:05:58.532 --> 00:06:00.584
By keeping my commandments.

00:06:00.584 --> 00:06:06.229
How many young people today keep
God's commandments, living in some

00:06:06.229 --> 00:06:11.874
emotional, misguided love, creating
love and declaring it by their own

00:06:11.874 --> 00:06:14.440
criteria, not by God's commandments.

00:06:14.440 --> 00:06:22.138
Jesus clearly says today, you will remain
in my love if you keep my commandments.

00:06:22.138 --> 00:06:28.809
We have believers, we have young
people who come to church, who follow

00:06:28.809 --> 00:06:33.940
and respect some commandments, but
have arbitrarily decided that some

00:06:33.940 --> 00:06:37.020
no longer morally apply to them.

00:06:37.400 --> 00:06:42.181
I have a question, can love
and morality be separated?

00:06:42.181 --> 00:06:44.571
Can love be against morality?

00:06:44.571 --> 00:06:46.005
No, it cannot.

00:06:46.005 --> 00:06:49.352
Love and morality are not in opposition.

00:06:49.352 --> 00:06:55.568
They go together, and that's why
it's necessary to follow all of God's

00:06:55.568 --> 00:06:58.436
commandments to remain in His love.

00:06:58.436 --> 00:07:04.652
You, my dears, are a generation that
doesn't let anyone tell you anything.

00:07:04.652 --> 00:07:10.389
There are fewer and fewer who
listen to their parents, and parents

00:07:10.389 --> 00:07:12.780
are the most sincere friends.

00:07:13.780 --> 00:07:18.543
Fewer and fewer people are listening
to the voice of the Gospel.

00:07:18.543 --> 00:07:22.910
Why should I be constrained
by norms or some moral code?

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:24.498
Live while you're young.

00:07:24.498 --> 00:07:26.483
That's how Saint Augustine thought.

00:07:26.483 --> 00:07:29.659
He lived in his time,
let's say, turbulently.

00:07:29.659 --> 00:07:32.835
He was driven by feelings,
driven by passion.

00:07:32.835 --> 00:07:38.790
Many young people today have nothing
else on their minds but to have a good

00:07:38.790 --> 00:07:45.142
time, to party, to joke around, to let
life pass by in who knows what, and

00:07:45.142 --> 00:07:48.715
then you go to bed with an empty heart.

00:07:49.520 --> 00:07:55.570
I feel so sorry for you sometimes, young
people, going to bed with empty hearts.

00:07:55.570 --> 00:08:01.216
You long for love so much, you
try so hard to attain it, but

00:08:01.216 --> 00:08:03.233
it slips through your fingers.

00:08:03.233 --> 00:08:08.073
It slips away because you're
looking for it in the wrong place.

00:08:08.073 --> 00:08:13.316
How hard you try to gain love, whether
it's friendship or romantic love.

00:08:13.316 --> 00:08:18.560
In the end, how many of you, young
people, are disappointed in love?

00:08:19.225 --> 00:08:25.061
How many of you have closed yourselves
off to love because you're afraid?

00:08:25.061 --> 00:08:31.345
And you have the right to be, if you've
been disappointed once, twice, three

00:08:31.345 --> 00:08:38.079
times, then you no longer allow anyone
to get close to you, not even God.

00:08:38.079 --> 00:08:42.569
Now, you see, Saint Augustine
lived through the same thing.

00:08:42.569 --> 00:08:48.853
However, at one point, he came to a
realization, and thanks to his mother's

00:08:48.853 --> 00:08:54.690
prayers, he himself said, "My heart
is restless until it rests in you."

00:08:56.330 --> 00:09:02.811
Today, telling a young person that they
can find all the answers, both in love and

00:09:02.811 --> 00:09:08.482
in life, through faith, they'll say you're
old-fashioned, that you live in the Middle

00:09:08.482 --> 00:09:11.317
Ages, what are you talking about, live.

00:09:11.317 --> 00:09:17.393
But I tell you, even Saint Augustine
said, there is no heart that will find

00:09:17.393 --> 00:09:23.064
peace, no person who will find their
peace without God, because we will always

00:09:23.064 --> 00:09:25.495
be restless, always missing that place.

00:09:25.495 --> 00:09:32.917
And so the question arises, well, Stjepan,
give us an answer on how we can grow

00:09:32.917 --> 00:09:35.700
in that love, don't just criticize.

00:09:35.700 --> 00:09:43.586
Well, my dears, the first thing you need
to do to start growing in love is to

00:09:43.586 --> 00:09:47.298
realize that you don't know how to love.

00:09:47.298 --> 00:09:52.400
The first step to growing in
love is to acknowledge that

00:09:52.400 --> 00:09:55.184
you don't know how to love.

00:09:55.184 --> 00:10:02.142
Love begins where you dare to admit
that you can't love on your own, and

00:10:02.142 --> 00:10:05.390
at that moment, God enters your heart.

00:10:05.690 --> 00:10:09.527
God then begins to enable you to love.

00:10:09.527 --> 00:10:14.803
That's why Saint Augustine says,
"Late have I loved you, beauty

00:10:14.803 --> 00:10:21.038
so old and so new." Dear young
people, I know it's sometimes hard

00:10:21.038 --> 00:10:27.274
to admit to yourself that you're
looking for love in the wrong place.

00:10:27.274 --> 00:10:33.030
I know it's sometimes hard to
admit that we beg for love.

00:10:33.030 --> 00:10:35.428
But let God teach you.

00:10:35.428 --> 00:10:41.184
We often recommend many guides on
love, five steps for this, four

00:10:41.184 --> 00:10:44.062
for that, three for something else.

00:10:44.062 --> 00:10:47.420
Let God teach you step by step.

00:10:48.200 --> 00:10:52.304
Not social media, not random
literature, not friendly advice,

00:10:52.304 --> 00:10:58.232
because someone is teaching you how
to love and advising you in your

00:10:58.232 --> 00:11:00.968
relationship with God or your neighbor.

00:11:00.968 --> 00:11:05.528
How to live, while they themselves
are wounded and unfulfilled.

00:11:05.528 --> 00:11:11.000
Have you ever heard someone who is
divorced speak beautifully about love?

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:16.016
Have you heard someone who is divorced
encourage others, saying, "Look,

00:11:16.016 --> 00:11:21.945
maybe I didn't know how to love,
but you try, you might succeed"?

00:11:22.705 --> 00:11:29.694
But many will often say, "Don't do
what I did." And that's not right.

00:11:29.694 --> 00:11:36.183
What's right is to admit that
maybe I didn't know how to love

00:11:36.183 --> 00:11:41.675
somewhere along the way, but that
doesn't mean others can't succeed.

00:11:41.675 --> 00:11:46.168
It doesn't mean everyone
should stop believing in love.

00:11:46.168 --> 00:11:49.662
So, how do you grow in love?

00:11:49.662 --> 00:11:54.655
You grow in love, my dears,
when you serve others.

00:11:55.155 --> 00:11:59.447
We have a very beautiful
example in Saint Joseph.

00:11:59.447 --> 00:12:04.693
Were the circumstances in which
Saint Joseph met Mary and in

00:12:04.693 --> 00:12:07.078
which she became pregnant ideal?

00:12:07.078 --> 00:12:13.754
Did they have all the security that
you seek today, like having a college

00:12:13.754 --> 00:12:19.954
degree, at least a small apartment, a
car, and then thinking about marriage?

00:12:19.954 --> 00:12:22.626
Did they have all the conditions?

00:12:22.626 --> 00:12:26.189
Did Joseph prepare everything
before marrying Mary, or

00:12:26.189 --> 00:12:28.861
did he have faith in God?

00:12:28.861 --> 00:12:33.759
He remained faithful to God,
and how did his love grow?

00:12:33.759 --> 00:12:36.876
By serving Mary and Jesus in silence.

00:12:36.876 --> 00:12:38.657
Love is often quiet.

00:12:38.657 --> 00:12:41.775
Love doesn't make a lot of noise.

00:12:41.775 --> 00:12:42.665
It serves.

00:12:42.665 --> 00:12:46.228
And the world today
can't handle that word.

00:12:46.228 --> 00:12:48.900
That's why I say, today's world...

00:12:49.350 --> 00:12:54.562
Glamour, noise, and entertainment
are often proclaimed as ideal love,

00:12:54.562 --> 00:13:00.818
but in reality, love is something
entirely different because it is quiet.

00:13:00.818 --> 00:13:04.988
It is not a feeling; it is service.

00:13:04.988 --> 00:13:08.637
Just look at Saint Joseph and Mary.

00:13:08.637 --> 00:13:14.893
Many of you are waiting for the
perfect time to create love.

00:13:14.893 --> 00:13:21.670
You need to prepare yourselves for love
first, and then create everything else.

00:13:22.510 --> 00:13:27.857
First, love happens to birds,
and then they build a nest.

00:13:27.857 --> 00:13:34.176
Not the other way around—building a
nest and then looking for a partner.

00:13:34.176 --> 00:13:36.606
So, love is often cruel.

00:13:36.606 --> 00:13:40.009
Today, I mentioned this saint, Saint Rita.

00:13:40.009 --> 00:13:46.329
She was born into a family in their
later years, where the parents

00:13:46.329 --> 00:13:49.731
prayed a lot to have that child.

00:13:49.731 --> 00:13:55.565
Even then, she was somehow a
sign from God to her parents.

00:13:55.885 --> 00:14:03.431
At that time, her parents promised her
to a husband who wasn't exactly an ideal

00:14:03.431 --> 00:14:06.450
example, a rough man without feelings.

00:14:06.450 --> 00:14:12.487
But back then, parental authority was
respected, and she honored it, even

00:14:12.487 --> 00:14:18.525
though she always wanted to enter
a convent rather than get married.

00:14:18.525 --> 00:14:24.562
However, she ended up with
such a man who was, let's say,

00:14:24.562 --> 00:14:26.574
rough, hard, and insensitive.

00:14:26.635 --> 00:14:33.131
And as I mentioned at the beginning
of the sermon, Saint Rita didn't

00:14:33.131 --> 00:14:39.128
choose whom she would marry, but
she chose how she would love.

00:14:39.128 --> 00:14:45.126
You young people today choose
whom you will marry, but few of

00:14:45.126 --> 00:14:48.124
you choose how you will love.

00:14:48.124 --> 00:14:54.621
That's why many get divorced, because
you choose, choose, spend so many years

00:14:54.621 --> 00:14:57.620
choosing, and still miss the mark.

00:14:57.819 --> 00:15:03.936
Because you haven't resolved things within
yourself, when you enter any relationship,

00:15:03.936 --> 00:15:10.563
be it a partnership, a monastery, a
marriage, whatever, how do you love?

00:15:10.563 --> 00:15:12.602
What happened to her?

00:15:12.602 --> 00:15:17.700
She decided to love, and
with her love, she converted,

00:15:17.700 --> 00:15:20.248
transformed such a rigid husband.

00:15:20.248 --> 00:15:23.817
Now, Jesus says, remain in my love.

00:15:23.817 --> 00:15:27.895
Her commitment was to
remain in God's love.

00:15:28.415 --> 00:15:33.166
And she soaked her husband
with God's love and succeeded.

00:15:33.166 --> 00:15:34.116
He converted.

00:15:34.116 --> 00:15:40.768
You know, her other misfortune was that
her husband died, that he was killed.

00:15:40.768 --> 00:15:42.669
She had two sons.

00:15:42.669 --> 00:15:47.895
And the sons, under the influence
of their uncle, wanted to

00:15:47.895 --> 00:15:49.796
avenge their father's death.

00:15:49.796 --> 00:15:56.448
And imagine a mother praying to God
that they would rather die than sin.

00:15:56.448 --> 00:16:02.150
That God would rather take them
than let them avenge their father.

00:16:02.460 --> 00:16:06.570
Rather than fall into grave
sin and end up in hell.

00:16:06.570 --> 00:16:09.934
Imagine a mother praying
for her children to die.

00:16:09.934 --> 00:16:11.802
But that is pure love.

00:16:11.802 --> 00:16:17.034
It sounds strange for a mother
to pray for her child to die, but

00:16:17.034 --> 00:16:19.650
she wanted to save them from hell.

00:16:19.650 --> 00:16:23.761
Today, we have mothers who relativize
their daughters' and sons' sins.

00:16:23.761 --> 00:16:28.620
They say, "What can I do? They
live in sin, it's their choice."

00:16:29.970 --> 00:16:35.305
Today, a mother might see that her
child is living in serious sin,

00:16:35.305 --> 00:16:40.229
perhaps addicted to drugs or something
else, but she won't help them.

00:16:40.229 --> 00:16:45.974
She stays silent so the neighbors
don't hear, so it's not known that the

00:16:45.974 --> 00:16:50.899
child is addicted to drugs, gambling,
or not living in premarital purity.

00:16:50.899 --> 00:16:52.951
Where have those mothers gone?

00:16:52.951 --> 00:16:57.055
Where is that love for
the soul of my child?

00:16:57.055 --> 00:17:01.979
Imagine that your child could end
up, God forbid, in hell tomorrow.

00:17:02.339 --> 00:17:08.078
Because no one prayed for
him to repent, to warn him.

00:17:08.078 --> 00:17:11.209
Look at everything that Rita did.

00:17:11.209 --> 00:17:17.991
She had such divine love within
her that she managed to convert the

00:17:17.991 --> 00:17:20.599
vulnerable person she lived with.

00:17:25.130 --> 00:17:32.847
Many imagine holiness as an ideal
state and a withdrawal from this world.

00:17:32.847 --> 00:17:38.190
However, holiness is realized
in all our concrete lives.

00:17:41.010 --> 00:17:44.227
There is no ideal time for holiness.

00:17:44.227 --> 00:17:48.823
Holiness is your moment that
you are living right now.

00:17:48.823 --> 00:17:53.879
It is encouraging to observe her
life, so martyr-like and suffering,

00:17:53.879 --> 00:17:58.935
but she fulfilled this command
of Jesus: Remain in my love.

00:17:59.054 --> 00:18:04.253
Whoever remains in God's love through the
greatest trials and sufferings, endures.

00:18:04.253 --> 00:18:10.750
Blessed Carlo Acutis from Assisi, the
saint in jeans, is dear to all of us.

00:18:10.750 --> 00:18:13.349
What did he say about love?

00:18:13.349 --> 00:18:19.847
You know that he suffered from leukemia
and that as a young man, with the

00:18:19.847 --> 00:18:26.345
little life he had, he was so in
love with God, so devoted to God,

00:18:26.345 --> 00:18:31.110
observing the sacraments and encouraging
others even when he needed help.

00:18:31.110 --> 00:18:33.744
What does he say about love?

00:18:33.744 --> 00:18:40.330
I die happy because I haven't wasted a
single minute on anything that isn't love.

00:18:43.560 --> 00:18:47.582
That's why many people, when
they encounter God, wouldn't

00:18:47.582 --> 00:18:49.818
want to leave the church.

00:18:49.818 --> 00:18:56.970
They used to go to church before, but
they didn't see Him, they didn't feel Him.

00:18:56.970 --> 00:19:02.334
Sometimes we spend a lot of
our lives in church, but we've

00:19:02.334 --> 00:19:04.122
wasted love somewhere else.

00:19:04.122 --> 00:19:10.827
And that's why I like his sentence, "I
die happy because I haven't wasted a

00:19:10.827 --> 00:19:15.744
single minute on anything that isn't
love." Holiness isn't about everything

00:19:15.744 --> 00:19:21.555
going your way, but about remaining God's
even when everything is falling apart.

00:19:21.555 --> 00:19:24.237
That's the message of today's saint.

00:19:24.237 --> 00:19:31.389
It's easy to be at peace in calm times,
easy to be in an ideal atmosphere.

00:19:31.389 --> 00:19:34.965
But when the cross, suffering,
or unforeseen circumstances

00:19:34.965 --> 00:19:37.200
come, that's when it matters.

00:19:38.120 --> 00:19:45.060
You, young people, don't consider
that in life, just like for all of

00:19:45.060 --> 00:19:50.933
us who are a bit older, you will
encounter unpredictable situations.

00:19:50.933 --> 00:19:55.738
In those situations, remember
what Saint Rita herself did.

00:19:55.738 --> 00:20:02.679
You then decide, if you are not
satisfied with that situation, how you

00:20:02.679 --> 00:20:05.882
will love to transform that situation.

00:20:05.882 --> 00:20:12.823
That's why I said, holiness is not about
everything happening as we imagined,

00:20:12.823 --> 00:20:19.230
but rather that in every situation
you go through, you remain God's.

00:20:19.550 --> 00:20:23.870
You remain with God, and
that is the greatest wisdom.

00:20:28.375 --> 00:20:36.660
When you look at the life of Saint
Rita, she had every possible reason to

00:20:36.660 --> 00:20:39.422
become bitter, to become disappointed.

00:20:39.422 --> 00:20:46.603
She had parents whom she loved,
that was the first blow, she lost

00:20:46.603 --> 00:20:53.232
her parents, her main support, then
her husband, then her two sons.

00:20:53.232 --> 00:20:59.308
So she had every reason to become
bitter, however... She chose

00:20:59.308 --> 00:21:03.175
differently, to be free and not bitter.

00:21:04.165 --> 00:21:10.205
Sometimes I feel that our believers choose
bitterness; they say they are believers,

00:21:10.205 --> 00:21:17.639
but they don't want to come out of their
bitterness, they don't want to come out

00:21:17.639 --> 00:21:21.356
of their wounds, they don't want to fight.

00:21:21.356 --> 00:21:23.679
Transform that wound of yours.

00:21:23.679 --> 00:21:27.396
Transform that pain, that
relationship, whatever happened to

00:21:27.396 --> 00:21:30.184
you, God's love can transform it.

00:21:30.184 --> 00:21:33.901
That's why it's important to stay in Him.

00:21:33.901 --> 00:21:41.799
Saint Rita, in the end, from her initial
dream as a child to become a nun and

00:21:41.799 --> 00:21:47.839
enter the convent, did get married and
went in a completely different direction.

00:21:47.839 --> 00:21:49.698
Were her dreams lost?

00:21:49.698 --> 00:21:53.879
No, God just fulfilled
them in a different way.

00:21:54.149 --> 00:21:58.312
At the end of her life,
she did enter the convent.

00:21:58.312 --> 00:22:02.096
Even though they didn't want
to accept her right away.

00:22:02.096 --> 00:22:05.124
She wanted to completely
dedicate herself to God.

00:22:05.124 --> 00:22:10.421
And she prayed to God to receive
a thorn on her forehead to remind

00:22:10.421 --> 00:22:12.692
her of His suffering and pain.

00:22:12.692 --> 00:22:14.205
And she received it.

00:22:14.205 --> 00:22:15.719
What is your thorn?

00:22:15.719 --> 00:22:20.639
Maybe you have a thorn in your
heart, maybe you have a thorn

00:22:20.639 --> 00:22:25.180
in your family, maybe you have a
thorn at university, be persistent.

00:22:25.620 --> 00:22:26.792
Because why?

00:22:26.792 --> 00:22:30.897
Because suffering and the
cross bring resurrection.

00:22:30.897 --> 00:22:36.761
Be a generation of saints, not
a generation of influencers.

00:22:36.761 --> 00:22:44.383
So be a generation of saints or holy
influencers, whatever you choose, but

00:22:44.383 --> 00:22:48.488
be those who bear witness to love.

00:22:48.488 --> 00:22:57.284
In the end, may her intercession and that
of all the other saints, especially Saint

00:22:57.284 --> 00:23:01.975
Anthony, guide us to remain in his love.

00:23:01.975 --> 00:23:02.655
Amen.

